Cursor Rule: Tailwind CSS & jQuery Only
Styling:
Use only Tailwind CSS utility classes for all UI and layout styling.
Do not write or edit any custom CSS files or <style> tags.
JavaScript:
Use only jQuery for all DOM manipulation, event handling, and AJAX.
Do not use vanilla JS, other frameworks, or custom JS libraries.
HTML:
Compose all markup using semantic HTML and Tailwind utility classes.
No inline styles or custom CSS classes.
Componentization:
If you need reusable UI, use HTML partials or jQuery-based rendering, not custom elements or frameworks.
Example:
 <button class="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-blue-600">Click me</button>
  <script>
    $(function() {
      $('button').on('click', function() {
        alert('Button clicked!');
      });
    });
  </script>